    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_3200507740" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3200507740" />
    <a title="Svetlana Barsik" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/110417954-svetlana-barsik"><img alt="Svetlana Barsik" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3200507740?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Svetlana Barsik" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Svetlana Barsik" href="/user/show/110417954-svetlana-barsik">Svetlana Barsik</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3200507740" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11377798891995618448"><p>I’ve devoured the first book yesterday, and just could not fall asleep, realizing that I had to get it off my chest before proceeding with the second book. I feel that my opinion of the characters will change dramatically.</p><p>I closed the book with the thought: &quot;Why on earth? What fools!&quot; They seemed to have reversed the polarity!</p><p>Well, let&apos;s start in order:</p><p>Valeria is a young woman, screwed-up by an early boring marriage with a worthless, parasitic fence-sitter as a husband who is an addicted gamer o</p></span>
  <span id="freeText11377798891995618448" style="display:none"><p>I’ve devoured the first book yesterday, and just could not fall asleep, realizing that I had to get it off my chest before proceeding with the second book. I feel that my opinion of the characters will change dramatically.</p><p>I closed the book with the thought: "Why on earth? What fools!" They seemed to have reversed the polarity!</p><p>Well, let's start in order:</p><p>Valeria is a young woman, screwed-up by an early boring marriage with a worthless, parasitic fence-sitter as a husband who is an addicted gamer on top of everything. She doesn’t experience neither love, nor passion, nor mutual understanding, nor help, nor care (even about a child!) in her marriage. They live like neighbors. She considers herself a puritan, but being tired of the indifference from her dull marriage, she pragmatically settles for a lasting adultery, selfishly accepting love and dedication from another man.</p><p>What motivated her? First, curiosity, then a thirst for pleasure, a need for affection and care, then a desire to at least warm up a little from the indifference of her husband in the rays of blind adoration and worship of a magnificent man. She only allowed him to love her, giving nothing in return. And as a result, she was scared to believe in Love and trust SUCH a man.</p><p>Here my sympathies are definitely in Alex’s favour! In addition to an ideal man standard qualities (successful, rich, handsome, sexy, aristocratic, sophisticated), HE KNOWS HOW TO LOVE! This is an example of a male who is able to really love, sincerely demonstrate how to WORSHIP a Woman, reverently adore her and be devoted to her wholeheartedly.</p><p><strong>This book is a manual “How to LOVE a Woman so that she "envies herself"</strong>!</p><p>After all, the stupid heroine did not appreciate this gift of fate in time.</p><p>
  <strong>When I want to plunge into the captivating world of tenderness, all-consuming passion, all-encompassing Love, I will return to the first book of "Monogamy", admiring such an ideal Men and such a genuine feeling.</strong>
</p><p>Conclusion:</p><p>For all the lovers of a beautiful plot and highly artful literature – read definitely! At first, you’ll choke on emotions, worrying about the heroes, devouring the entire book. And then, slowly and relishing every phrase, re-read it more than once! Thank you, Victoria, for an exciting book! I am delighted with your ability to present this story saturated with eroticism, but not in a smutty way and without details. It is passionate, sensual, colorful, and captivating. Thank you for the hours of enjoyment with Monogamy!</p><p>P.S. Thank you, Victoria, for an ARC provided for my honest review!<em></em> </p></span>
  <a data-text-id="11377798891995618448" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


