  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3197994397" />
    <a title="Helen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/110355411-helen"><img alt="Helen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1582143320p2/110355411.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3197994397?book_show_action=true">Feb 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Helen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Helen" href="/user/show/110355411-helen">Helen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3197994397" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17759451812909669097"><p>READ THIS BOOK! EVERYONE!</p><p>
  <br/>
</p><p>It’s extremely rare for me to write reviews or even share comments. I do it exceptionally only if the book hits a nerve, and I simply don’t have the strength to remain silent.</p><p>
  <br/>
</p><p>This is exactly the case with this masterpiece. I’d like to drag everyone into this boundless torment of emotions, into this joy.</p><p>
  <br/>
</p><p>This is a rare case when a book settles in your soul so much, when you start living one life with the heroes, you are so imbued with their experiences that it </p></span>
  <span id="freeText17759451812909669097" style="display:none"><p>READ THIS BOOK! EVERYONE!</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>It’s extremely rare for me to write reviews or even share comments. I do it exceptionally only if the book hits a nerve, and I simply don’t have the strength to remain silent.</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>This is exactly the case with this masterpiece. I’d like to drag everyone into this boundless torment of emotions, into this joy.</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>This is a rare case when a book settles in your soul so much, when you start living one life with the heroes, you are so imbued with their experiences that it hurts in your chest, you have a lump in your throat.</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>It is impossible to tear yourself away from reading, because you wait that they will be fine in the next chapter, everything will come to end meaningfully. “<strong><em>This book just has to be read, otherwise you’ll be missing out on something very important</em></strong>!” – Yes! Definitely so!</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>P.S. The author sent me the book for my honest review, thank you very much ♡</p></span>
