<div id="review_3201937205" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3201937205" />
    <a title="Oxana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/110477403-oxana"><img alt="Oxana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1582837660p2/110477403.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3201937205?book_show_action=true">Feb 22, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Oxana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Oxana" href="/user/show/110477403-oxana">Oxana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51475154-monogamy-book-one-lover">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3201937205" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13767893274627467843"><p>I stumbled upon this book by accident, the title hooked me and then the prologue... I decided to check it out: will I like it from the very beginning?</p><p>“<em>I rise to the surface first, take a breath and then go back, pushing her upwards. She is exhausted, her arms like jelly, her movements slow.</em></p><p>
  <em>My hands on her hips, I keep pushing... for her to breathe, for her to make it...</em>
</p><p>
  <em>And she does, she no longer needs me. I could let go, she’s okay, she’s breathing!</em>
</p><p>
  <em>I could but I don’t, because I can </em></p></span>
  <span id="freeText13767893274627467843" style="display:none"><p>I stumbled upon this book by accident, the title hooked me and then the prologue... I decided to check it out: will I like it from the very beginning?</p><p>“<em>I rise to the surface first, take a breath and then go back, pushing her upwards. She is exhausted, her arms like jelly, her movements slow.</em></p><p>
  <em>My hands on her hips, I keep pushing... for her to breathe, for her to make it...</em>
</p><p>
  <em>And she does, she no longer needs me. I could let go, she’s okay, she’s breathing!</em>
</p><p>
  <em>I could but I don’t, because I can feel her stomach beneath my lips, clenching desperately with each breath. I kiss it lightly, a single touch, forgetting that I, too, must breath, must rise up and fill my lungs with air if I want to live. But in that moment, I feel more alive than ever and I don’t need air. There is something else giving me life, filling me till my ears ring. My heart is trying to break out of my chest and I can barely breathe from the emotion, the effort, the desire to do something, run somewhere, accomplish anything... to prove that I’m worthy, that I can be everything she needs.</em>
</p><p><em> ‘I want to be yours...</em>’”</p><p>To tell you “I liked it” .... is just wrong. It’s a <strong>magnificent book</strong>! I read it in 2 days. I was lost for this world. It is written as if you are watching a movie.</p><p>There is such an expression "mind blowing", well, that’s it for me. It was some kind of an emotional roller coaster!</p><p>I enjoyed the plot so much, I was engrossed with the characters’ actions. I am surprised with the author’s ability to create such heroes. They are vivid, and you just know that they exist! You believe in their actions, in their feelings. I was worried about Valery and Alex for all the 200 pages!</p><p>And I honestly admit, I periodically wanted to postpone the book for I was tormented by the thought that I would finish reading ... but I didn’t want to! I enjoyed it too much!</p><p>The book kept me on edge till the very end, but even after reading it I can’t let it go. I am HUGELY impressed!</p><p>Thank you author for this romance!<em></em> </p></span>
  <a data-text-id="13767893274627467843" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


