<div id="review_3205864070" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3205864070" />
    <a title="Anased" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/110587886-anased"><img alt="Anased" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3205864070?book_show_action=true">Feb 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anased" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anased" href="/user/show/110587886-anased">Anased</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51475154-monogamy-book-one-lover">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3205864070" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6663503430760321442"><p>About a month has passed since I finished the book, but the characters from Monogamy don’t let me go.</p><p>
  <br/>
</p><p>“<em>Sometimes we supposedly grown-up people are as blind as newborn kittens. Our vision is inevitably obscured by someone else’s negative experience, an unwanted opinion, the moralising of both those close to us and indifferent strangers, and we are prevented from seeing the shortest and straightest road to unlimited happiness. But whatever fate has in store has already been mapped out by a high</em></p></span>
  <span id="freeText6663503430760321442" style="display:none"><p>About a month has passed since I finished the book, but the characters from Monogamy don’t let me go.</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>“<em>Sometimes we supposedly grown-up people are as blind as newborn kittens. Our vision is inevitably obscured by someone else’s negative experience, an unwanted opinion, the moralising of both those close to us and indifferent strangers, and we are prevented from seeing the shortest and straightest road to unlimited happiness. But whatever fate has in store has already been mapped out by a higher power</em>.”</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>My thoughts are constantly returning to this book, I can’t find what hooked me.</p><p>The life experience? Well, yes. A lot of people’ve had (or are experiencing it now, or maybe will meet it in future) THAT ONE AND ONLY love. Only not every partner was SO motivated. The plot in this book is rather a dream come true. Yes, despite the fact that the main male character is a very complex person.</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>“<em>It feels as if Alex is deliberately giving out as little information about himself as possible, that he is merely creating the illusion of openness. Yet it is clear to me that his personality is as deep as the Mariana Trench. Its darkness and mystery beckon, and the desire to get closer is becoming increasingly powerful.</em></p><p><em>Skipping ahead, this habit of his to communicate in hints, to force people to read between the lines, and doing it himself will cause a great deal of damage to both of us</em>.”</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>I put a lot of effort into acceptance of the heroes’ actions. It was not just acceptance, more like a realization of its correctness and logic.</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>“<em>There are people who don’t know how to be happy. When fate throws expensive gifts their way, they look for the catch. Distrustful, they steer clear. Yet knowing how to accept such gifts with gratitude is more important than anything our parents and teachers instil in us as children. No one is going to tell you why you’re here, what your purpose is, what you’re searching for, and what to do with what you find</em>.”</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>This book is the parallel universe of which almost every woman dreams. Careful with your dreams, they sometimes come true! ☝</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>❤<em>The ARC is provided by the author for an honest review</em> ❤</p></span>
  <a data-text-id="6663503430760321442" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
