<div id="review_3203349320" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3203349320" />
    <a title="Olga" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/110516334-olga"><img alt="Olga" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3203349320?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Olga" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Olga" href="/user/show/110516334-olga">Olga</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51475154-monogamy-book-one-lover">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3203349320" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1187607114591353711"><p>“<em>It was love - the brightest of all emotions, the deepest of all my feelings, the largest of all my meanings, the reason why I was born and lived, until I met her...</em>”</p><p>
  <br/>
</p><p>This is the story of a lifetime of two people who love each other forever. How much have they endured! I was angry and I hated, cheered and loved along with the heroes. There were times when it came to tears in my eyes because of hopelessness, and then from happiness. I just don’t know how to express what I’m experiencing now af</p></span>
  <span id="freeText1187607114591353711" style="display:none"><p>“<em>It was love - the brightest of all emotions, the deepest of all my feelings, the largest of all my meanings, the reason why I was born and lived, until I met her...</em>”</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>This is the story of a lifetime of two people who love each other forever. How much have they endured! I was angry and I hated, cheered and loved along with the heroes. There were times when it came to tears in my eyes because of hopelessness, and then from happiness. I just don’t know how to express what I’m experiencing now after the end of the book.</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>“<em>Very soon, it becomes clear to me, in the most incomprehensible, most incredible way, that he is seriously in love. It is the only time I have a question that I cannot find an answer to for a very long time, no matter how hard I try: what does he see in me? What?? What exactly does he find so irresistible? My analytical brain comes up with the most outrageous suggestions, but, for the very first time, gets nowhere</em>.”</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>For a long time I have not experienced so many emotions! Having started reading this book, I turned into a creature lost to the world for a day. As an addict, I read page after page, trying to find out what was next. And when the book was over, I sat and thought: How? Is that all? I want more!</p><p>
  <br />
</p><p>❧<em>The ARC is provided by the author for an honest review.</em> ​</p></span>
