<div id="review_3197307475" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3197307475" />
    <a title="Anna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/110330853-anna"><img alt="Anna" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3197307475?book_show_action=true">Feb 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anna" href="/user/show/110330853-anna">Anna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3197307475" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14183934840012315265"><p>～<em>The ARC is provided by the author for an honest review.</em> ～</p><p>I’ve finished it! Finally! I <strong>fell out of life for 2 days</strong>! I hated the heroine (b*tches be crazy), wept, (prayed - dear, please, don’t die), rejoiced, and then sobbed again. I read a lot, and I have many favorite books that I re-read more than once, but I can’t re-read this one - it evokes overly strong emotions, and <strong>you just don’t mess with your pressure</strong>. But it certainly will be one of my favorites. And how beautifully this book is writt</p></span>
  <span id="freeText14183934840012315265" style="display:none"><p>～<em>The ARC is provided by the author for an honest review.</em> ～</p><p>I’ve finished it! Finally! I <strong>fell out of life for 2 days</strong>! I hated the heroine (b*tches be crazy), wept, (prayed - dear, please, don’t die), rejoiced, and then sobbed again. I read a lot, and I have many favorite books that I re-read more than once, but I can’t re-read this one - it evokes overly strong emotions, and <strong>you just don’t mess with your pressure</strong>. But it certainly will be one of my favorites. And how beautifully this book is written, there is so much tenderness beyond words in it. You feel so deeply through it <strong>that it’s impossible to forget this book</strong>. Many thanks to the author.</p></span>
