        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51475154-monogamy-book-one-lover">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3211034838" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17503609657755916419">Monogamy is more than just a love story; it starts as a classic love story with a common plot, but the author has the depth and the wisdom to go beyond the ordinary, especially in the vivid description of Valera&apos;s soul torments. Valeria is the embodiment of those who try very hard their whole life to do the right thing by ignoring their heart&apos;s desire. Through a subtle and tender diagnosis of Valeria&apos;s struggles, the author proves to be a discreet observer of human&apos;s heart. She is also a master </span>
  <span id="freeText17503609657755916419" style="display:none">Monogamy is more than just a love story; it starts as a classic love story with a common plot, but the author has the depth and the wisdom to go beyond the ordinary, especially in the vivid description of Valera's soul torments. Valeria is the embodiment of those who try very hard their whole life to do the right thing by ignoring their heart's desire. Through a subtle and tender diagnosis of Valeria's struggles, the author proves to be a discreet observer of human's heart. She is also a master of detailed descriptions of the architecture and landscapes. Throughout the whole book, you experience a roller-coaster of emotions, along with the two main characters, who love, struggle and fight to find their inner peace. I would definitely recommend this book and I can't wait for the next part of Valeria's journey. The author sent me the book for my honest review. Thank you a lot!</span>
