<div id="review_3216588180" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3216588180" />
    <a title="Виктория Манукян" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/106436912"><img alt="Виктория Манукян" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3216588180?book_show_action=true">Mar 03, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Виктория Манукян" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Виктория Манукян" href="/user/show/106436912">Виктория Манукян</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3216588180" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8291356747561211729">I read the Monogamy on the recommendation, but I started it blindly without any understanding of what it is about. And for some reason, the first thought based on the name was that it’s something about psychology. I began to read out of curiosity and did not notice that on the very first evening I’ve finished half of the book. Time flew by, it was impossible to tear myself away from the book! From the first pages my emotions were over the edge.I got so used to them, imagined everything to the sm</span>
  <span id="freeText8291356747561211729" style="display:none">I read the Monogamy on the recommendation, but I started it blindly without any understanding of what it is about. And for some reason, the first thought based on the name was that it’s something about psychology. I began to read out of curiosity and did not notice that on the very first evening I’ve finished half of the book. Time flew by, it was impossible to tear myself away from the book! From the first pages my emotions were over the edge.I got so used to them, imagined everything to the smallest detail and it seemed that I was not reading, but living some kind of reality. Even when there was no time for reading, thoughts about Valeria and Alex did not get out of my head.It’s a very emotional and sensual love story. It has everything: an intelligent plot, strong characters, tenderness, joy, sorrow, the destiny of two souls meant for each other and ETERNAL LOVE…Ever since my school when there were no electronic books, I always read with a pencil in my hand. I highlighted the quotes I liked. This book is highlighted by me through and through. So many wise words which unfortunately come only with age and experience! Monogamy makes you experience a storm of emotions and delight!Don’t hurt those you love, because such hurt will never be forgotten. It will grind your feelings into dust and you’ll either spend the rest of your life walking in it or waste what little time you have on earth searching for something else. And there’s no guarantee you’ll find it. Sometimes we supposedly grown-up people are as blind as newborn kittens. Our vision is inevitably obscured by someone else’s negative experience, an unwanted opinion, the moralising of both those close to us and indifferent strangers, and we are prevented from seeing the shortest and straightest road to unlimited happiness. But whatever fate has in store has already been mapped out by a higher power. There are people who don’t know how to be happy. When fate throws expensive gifts their way, they look for the catch. Distrustful, they steer clear. Yet knowing how to accept such gifts with gratitude is more important than anything our parents and teachers instil in us as children. No one is going to tell you why you’re here, what your purpose is, what you’re searching for, and what to do with what you find. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8291356747561211729" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


