<div id="review_3567621866" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3567621866" />
    <a title="Kris" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/88030059-kris"><img alt="Kris" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576816281p2/88030059.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3567621866?book_show_action=true">Oct 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kris" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kris" href="/user/show/88030059-kris">Kris</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51475154-monogamy-book-one-lover">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/88030059-kris?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/88030059-kris?shelf=own">own</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3567621866" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14179607478846602885">Wow.<br/>Stunningly well-written. <br/>Sensual from start to end.<br/>Emotionally charged.<br/>Raw &amp; honest.<br/>Author to watch. <br/><br/>The incredible way Sobolev uses words to describe simple things, like a picnic in the park becomes so charged with feeling; when it seems all she is doing is describing the interaction between two people ~ and HOW! Sobolov extends a moment in time to where you experience every nuance along with Valeria. <br/><br/>There are secrets that unfold. Tension builds in a masterful way. I was curious to see whe</span>
  <span id="freeText14179607478846602885" style="display:none">Wow.<br />Stunningly well-written. <br />Sensual from start to end.<br />Emotionally charged.<br />Raw &amp; honest.<br />Author to watch. <br /><br />The incredible way Sobolev uses words to describe simple things, like a picnic in the park becomes so charged with feeling; when it seems all she is doing is describing the interaction between two people ~ and HOW! Sobolov extends a moment in time to where you experience every nuance along with Valeria. <br /><br />There are secrets that unfold. Tension builds in a masterful way. I was curious to see where Sobolev went with infidelity &amp; love; but, this blew away all expectation. I found myself rooting for Valeria &amp; Alex; and, I've been married for 34 yrs.<br /><br />This is far and away my favorite favorite Romance, Pych Thriller &amp; overall Women's Lit. <br />The only downside? You will be abruptly left hanging like in Fifty Shades but in a much more masterful way. So, you'll absolutely have to buy the sequel to find out more. All I can say: Sobolev, WRITE FASTER! You know a book is good, when you anticipate re-reading it right before the sequel comes out, just to re-live the romance~<br /><br />Fabulous~ just, Brilliant!</span>
  <a data-text-id="14179607478846602885" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
