  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3269350459?book_show_action=true">Apr 08, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melina Lobo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melina Lobo" href="/user/show/88375090-melina-lobo">Melina Lobo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51475154-monogamy-book-one-lover">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3269350459&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3269350459" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8634952649840200337">Have you ever wondered what role physical compatibility plays in relationships?<br/>🦄🦄🦄<br/>Valeria was forced into a marriage when she became pregnant, so she&apos;s never known what true love felt like.<br/>Until, she met Alex, a handsome stranger who wandered into her life and brought passion and love along with him.<br/>Their relationship is a fiery fairytale, but all fairytales do not have happy endings.<br/>‘When you fall in love, you love forever - it’s in our family blood. Look for HER and you’ll find your happiness </span>
  <span id="freeText8634952649840200337" style="display:none">Have you ever wondered what role physical compatibility plays in relationships?<br />🦄🦄🦄<br />Valeria was forced into a marriage when she became pregnant, so she's never known what true love felt like.<br />Until, she met Alex, a handsome stranger who wandered into her life and brought passion and love along with him.<br />Their relationship is a fiery fairytale, but all fairytales do not have happy endings.<br />‘When you fall in love, you love forever - it’s in our family blood. Look for HER and you’ll find your happiness beyond thought…’<br />🦄🦄🦄<br />Monogamy Lover by Victoria Sobolev is the first book in the Monogamy series.<br />I have conflicted feelings about this book because Valeria and Alex obviously have a deep connection, physically and mentally, but she's MARRIED and I know that's the whole basis of this story but she what irked me was that she has a kid.<br />My brain and my heart are not sure if they can settle on this matter because it hurts to know that someone might be your soulmate but at the same time you can't do anything about it.<br />Valeria has insecurity issues that she finds only Alex can resolve. As a wife (obviously not the best) but what triggered me the most is when she brought Alex around her son. <br />Her affections for Alex are apparent at the end and so is her loyalty to him.<br />Alex is probably every woman's dreamboat, and it's more than obvious he loves her through his gestures but sometimes I had a feeling he was just stringing her along? We only get Valeria's point of view so I'm not really sure what's going on in his head.<br />In some ways I do see why Valeria would resort to cheating because they both have had rough paste and when they find each other it's like a breath of fresh air.<br />On a personal level, yes I did have quite a few things that personally are not my favourite but the story in itself isn't bad.<br />The author's writing, plot and storytelling capabilities are great and she knows just how far to push the plot but keep you hanging for more so you continue to read because of the emotions in it.<br />The cliffhanger was unexpected, she has written a great ending to start an even better beginning for the next book in the series.<br />🦄🦄🦄<br />Rated 8.5/10<br />Melina L.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8634952649840200337" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


