<div id="review_3576457445" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3576457445" />
    <a title="Mulan Book Princess" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/116287253-mulan-book-princess"><img alt="Mulan Book Princess" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3576457445?book_show_action=true">Oct 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mulan Book Princess" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mulan Book Princess" href="/user/show/116287253-mulan-book-princess">Mulan Book Princess</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/116287253-mulan-book-princess?shelf=cheating">cheating</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3576457445" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17119306015548309690">Hmmm ... I have to say I am a bit torn. I love how Valeria and Alex has this intense attraction and connection to each other, but technically she is married even though her husband may not be the love of her life. To be fair, her marriage should’ve ended before anything started. But then again, Alex is the love of her life...oh the morals conflict!! I normally don’t read any stories that have cheating but got a bit mislead by the title. That being said, the book was beautifully written, and the </span>
  <span id="freeText17119306015548309690" style="display:none">Hmmm ... I have to say I am a bit torn. I love how Valeria and Alex has this intense attraction and connection to each other, but technically she is married even though her husband may not be the love of her life. To be fair, her marriage should’ve ended before anything started. But then again, Alex is the love of her life...oh the morals conflict!! I normally don’t read any stories that have cheating but got a bit mislead by the title. That being said, the book was beautifully written, and the love between the two was so touching. If you are okay with the relationship while one person is married, then this is a great book. If you can’t get past the cheating, this book is not for you.<br /><br />I received a free advanced review copy of this book and am voluntarily leaving a fair and honest review.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17119306015548309690" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


